President Donald Trump has issued a proclamation recognizing National School Lunch Week, which aims to acknowledge the benefits of school lunch programs in providing nutritious meals to children. The National School Lunch Program provides low-cost or free meals to approximately 30 million students each year, ensuring they receive the nourishment they need to succeed academically and physically. The proclamation emphasizes the importance of returning control of school meals to the local level and supporting school nutrition specialists and food service professionals. The President calls upon all Americans to participate in activities that promote awareness of the health and well-being of the nation's children.